  , issueCommentBody =
      "No matter what I tried, on a Ubuntu 13.10 upgrade, the following would fail for npm:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsudo apt-get install g++ protobuf-compiler protobuf-c-compiler libprotobuf-dev libv8-dev libgoogle-perftools-dev make libprotoc-dev libboost-dev python-pip python-dev libyaml-dev nodejs npm git-core libtinfo-dev\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf, however, I installed npm separately like so:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsudo apt-get install g++ protobuf-compiler protobuf-c-compiler libprotobuf-dev\r\nlibv8-dev libgoogle-perftools-dev make libprotoc-dev libboost-dev\r\npython-pip python-dev libyaml-dev nodejs git-core libtinfo-dev\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\nsudo apt-get install npm\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis succeeded.\r\n\r\nI was prompted to use\r\n\r\n```\r\n./configure --fetch protoc\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis failed. I had to also:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsudo apt-get install libncurses5-dev\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen I got issue with nodejs permissions, so I installed this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsudo apt-get install nodejs-legacy\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen ran:\r\n\r\n```\r\nsudo make\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd it compiled successfully."
